%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20Saturday%20in%20October%201973%20when%20Arab%20armies%20launched%20a%20massive%20surprise%20attack%20that%20came%20perilously%20close%20to%20defeating%20Israel.%20And%20it%20was%20Saturday%20in%20October%202023%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20surprise%20assault%20across%20the%20Gaza%20border%20that%20killed%20more%20than%201%2C300%20Israelis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wars%20of%201973%20and%202023%20have%20more%20in%20common%20than%20timing.%20Both%20are%20textbook%20examples%20of%20strategic%20surprise%20and%20the%20devastating%20cost%20of%20overconfidence%2C%20complacency%2C%20and%20wishful%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20both%20cases%2C%20Israel%20appeared%20convinced%20that%20it%20could%20easily%20defeat%20any%20enemy%20invasion%20and%20that%20its%20enemies%20knew%20this%20and%20therefore%20wouldn't%20attack.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6322802%2Fyom-kippur-war-israel-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1973%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20price%20of%20that%20miscalculation%20was%20almost%203%2C000%20soldiers%20killed%20from%20an%20Israeli%20force%20of%20about%20400%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20toll%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F16%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-hamas-gaza-war-explained-week-2-mime-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHamas'%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Israel%20this%20month%20was%20about%201%2C300%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20were%20civilians%2C%20and%20casualties%20%E2%80%94%20combatants%20and%20civilians%20%E2%80%94%20will%20only%20increase%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-has-tools-to-counter-hamas-drones-but-may-struggle-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3EIsrael%20launches%20an%20invasion%20of%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Israel%20tank%20Golan%20Heights%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65328177be9edfa8eda5bdbe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Israeli%20tank%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20during%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War.%3Cp%3EHenri%20Bureau%2FSygma%2FCorbis%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%20ended%20after%20nearly%20three%20weeks%20of%20fighting.%20Egyptian%20President%20Anwar%20Sadat%2C%20satisfied%20that%20Egypt's%20humiliation%20in%20the%201967%20Six-Day%20War%20had%20been%20redeemed%2C%20eventually%20signed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upi.com%2FNews_Photos%2Fview%2Fupi%2F86f0514419ff6655c4d2947f1dacd91f%2FCarter-Sadat-and-Begin-shake-hands-at-Camp-David-peace-treaty-negotiations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Camp%20David%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Israel%20in%201978.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEgypt%20got%20back%20the%20Sinai%2C%20and%20Israel%20made%20peace%20with%20its%20most%20powerful%20enemy.%20Even%20if%20the%20peace%20is%20frigid%2C%20it's%20been%20a%20half-century%20since%20Israelis%20and%20Egyptians%20met%20in%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20specter%20of%20another%20regional%20war%20now%20hovering%20over%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20that%20outcome%20may%20be%20comforting%20to%20those%20struggling%20with%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Gaza%20war.%20If%20Israel%20and%20Egypt%20could%20make%20peace%2C%20why%20not%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20that%20hope%20is%20largely%20misplaced.%20The%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%20was%20a%20war%20between%20nations%20employing%20regular%20armies%20that%20fought%20intense%20mechanized%20battles%20like%20those%20of%20World%20War%20II.%20The%20goals%20of%20the%20combatants%20were%20limited%3A%20Egypt%20wanted%20Sinai%2C%20Syria%20wanted%20the%20Golan%2C%20and%20Israel%20wanted%20to%20restore%20its%20military%20reputation%20and%20establish%20deterrence%20with%20its%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Israel%20soldiers%20Golan%20Heights%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532817696f7540cd06164da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221300%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIsraeli%20troops%20and%20artillery%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights%20on%20October%2017%2C%201973.%3Cp%3EFred%20Ihrt%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIsraelis%20in%201973%20did%20believe%20they%20were%20fighting%20for%20their%20survival.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20it%20seemed%20as%20if%20Syrian%20tanks%20would%20break%20out%20of%20the%20Golan%20and%20advance%20on%20Haifa.%20In%20a%20panic%20over%20heavy%20Israeli%20losses%2C%20Defense%20Minister%20Moshe%20Dayan%20urged%20Prime%20Minister%20Golda%20Meir%20to%20consider%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fdayan-pushed-pm-meir-to-consider-using-nuclear-weapons-in-1973%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enuclear%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20after%20the%20war%20ended%2C%20some%20Israelis%20were%20convinced%20the%20Arabs%20would%20rearm%20with%20Soviet%20weapons%20and%20attack%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20did%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%20ultimately%20result%20in%20Israel%20signing%20a%20peace%20treaty%20%E2%80%94%20which%20included%20returning%20the%20Sinai%20buffer%20zone%20%E2%80%94%20and%20achieving%20a%20mostly%20stable%20ceasefire%20with%20Syria%3F%20Because%20the%20stakes%20were%20not%20so%20high%20that%20there%20wasn't%20room%20for%20negotiation%20and%20compromise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20case%20with%20Hamas%20and%20Israel.%20Hamas%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Fwhat-hamas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20refused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20recognize%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20which%20it%20says%20occupies%20what%20it%20deems%20Islamic%20lands.%20At%20most%2C%20it%20seems%20willing%20to%20offer%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fid%2Fwbna24235665%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bhudna%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20truce%20with%20the%20implication%20that%20violence%20could%20resume%20at%20any%20moment.%20With%20such%20maximalist%20goals%2C%20there%20seems%20little%20room%20for%20compromise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20is%20that%20Israel%20is%20safer%20than%20it%20was%20in%201973.%20Hamas%20or%20Hezbollah%20might%20briefly%20seize%20some%20border%20territory%20and%20take%20hostages%2C%20but%20there%20is%20little%20chance%20of%20Arab%20armies%20conquering%20Israel.%20However%2C%20Hamas%20does%20have%20the%20capability%20to%20use%20rockets%20and%20terror%20attacks%20to%20wage%20a%20low-level%20war%20and%20disrupt%20everyday%20life%20in%20Israel%2C%20a%20Western-style%20nation%20with%20an%20advanced%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Israel%20artillery%20shells%20white%20phosphorus%20Sderot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532817796f7540cd06164e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIsraeli%20troops%20with%20artillery%20shells%20labeled%20D528%2C%20the%20US%20military%20code%20for%20%26quot%3Bwhite%20phosphorus-based%20munitions%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20Sderot%20on%20October%209.%3Cp%3EMostafa%20Alkharouf%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201973%2C%20Israel%20could%20use%20its%20military%20to%20achieve%20tangible%20goals.%20After%20a%20grueling%2019-day%20war%2C%20the%20IDF%20advanced%20to%20within%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Freversal-of-fortune-how-the-idf-turned-the-yom-kippur-war-around%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estriking%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Cairo%20and%20Damascus%2C%20inducing%20their%20enemies%20to%20accept%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20an%20option%20in%20Gaza.%20Israel%20can't%20force%20Hamas%20militants%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-invasion-gaza-hamas-hardest-fighting-underground-tunnels-warfare-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20engage%20in%20open%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E%20nor%20can%20it%20send%20in%20its%20police%20to%20arrest%20them.%20Like%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%2C%20Hamas%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Fwhat-hamas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreaded%20through%3C%2Fa%3E%20political%20and%20social%20life%20in%20Gaza%2C%20functioning%20as%20a%20government%2C%20an%20army%2C%20and%20a%20terror%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20leaves%20no%20good%20long-term%20options.%20Israel%20can't%20use%20aerial%20bombardment%20to%20destroy%20Hamas'%20military%20capabilities%20without%20also%20inflicting%20civilian%20casualties%20that%20would%20inflame%20world%20opinion.%20Reoccupying%20Gaza%20would%20require%20a%20counterinsurgency%20that%20would%20be%20a%20nightmare%20for%20Israeli%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20a%20buffer%20zone%20inside%20Gaza%20is%20an%20option%20to%20preclude%20another%20Hamas%20ground%20invasion%2C%20but%20it%20would%20require%20a%20considerable%20troop%20presence%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20stop%20Hamas%20from%20launching%20rockets%20that%20have%20hit%20as%20far%20away%20as%20northern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Israel%20Golda%20Meir%20Egypt%20Anwar%20Sadat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6532817696f7540cd06164dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221749%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Golda%20Meir%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Egyptian%20President%20Anwar%20El%20S