0Union%20government%20and%20other%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsking%20all%20stakeholders%20to%20therefore%20%E2%80%9Cstrictly%20adhere%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20counselling%20session%20fixed%20by%20the%20NMC%20for%20the%20academic%20session%20of%202023-24%20for%20the%20undergraduate%20MBBS%20course%2C%20the%20notification%20issued%20by%20Shambhu%20Sharan%20Kumar%2C%20director%20of%20undergraduate%20medical%20education%20board%2C%20said%20those%20who%20were%20accommodated%20after%20the%20September%2030%20deadline%20would%20be%20declared%20invalid%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20students%20admitted%2C%20if%20any%2C%20shall%20be%20discharged%20immediately%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumar%20also%20underlined%20that%20in%202019%2C%20the%20SC%20had%20stated%20that%20seats%20lying%20vacant%20would%20not%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjustifiable%20reason%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20institutes%20to%20extend%20the%20cut-off%20date%20or%20allow%20admissions%20beyond%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20such%20students%20were%20asked%20to%20go%2C%20hundreds%20of%20MBBS%20seats%20would%20remain%20vacant%20across%20the%20country%2C%20unless%20the%20SC%20further%20extends%20the%20September%2030%20deadline.%20Most%20of%20the%20students%20who%20are%20to%20lose%20their%20admission%20had%20responded%20to%20the%20advertisements%20put%20out%20by%20medical%20colleges%20seeking%20admission.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fchennai%2F600-mbbs-students-to-lose-seats-in-nmc-crackdown%2Farticleshow%2F104592879.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bihar%20Combined%20Entrance%20Competitive%20Examination%20Board%20had%20advertised%20on%20October%209%20inviting%20applications%20for%20a%20stray%20vacancy%20round.%E2%80%9D%20The%20report%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COfficials%20in%20Bengal%20said%20the%20number%20of%20vacant%20seats%20was%20still%20