e%20entire%20funding%20is%20provided%20by%20the%20government.%20And%20the%20answer%20is%20%E2%80%93%20it%20takes%20both%20hands%20to%20clap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20has%20been%20seen%20time%20and%20again%2C%20the%20projects%20that%20work%20best%20are%20those%20where%20the%20private%20and%20public%20sector%20come%20together%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20a%20former%20NITI%20Aayog%20official.%20He%20says%20that%20the%20private%20or%20civil%20society%20players%20bring%20efficiencies%20and%20levels%20of%20competence%20that%20government%20players%20often%20lack.%20Chandra%20echoes%20this%20sentiment%20in%20reverse%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20scale%20government%20can%20provide%2C%20no%20private%20sector%20player%20can%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20even%20while%20the%20state%20government%20is%20willing%20to%20finance%20almost%20the%20entire%20effort%2C%20the%20A.T.E.%20CF%20identifies%2C%20monitors%20and%20assists%20the%20NGOs%20that%20work%20on%20the%20ground.%20It%20has%20also%20lent%20its%20technology%20app%20to%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20to%20collect%20real%20time%20data%20on%20all%20the%20water%20rejuvenation%20sites%20across%20the%20state%20from%20the%20Mantralaya%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20to%20prioritise%20where%20such%20work%20needs%20to%20commence%20right%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20foundation%20also%20provides%20regular%20weekly%20training%20for%20the%20nodal%20government%20officers%20with%20use%20of%20the%20app%20and%20any%20glitches%20that%20may%20arise.%20Besides%20setting%20up%20a%20project%20management%20unit%2C%20the%20foundation%E2%80%99s%20chief%20operating%20officer%20(COO)%20Gayatri%20Nair%20Lobo%2C%20has%20made%2024%20field%20trips%20to%20six%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Karnataka%20since%20April%202022%20alone.%20In%20a%20country%20as%20vast%2C%20diverse%20and%20complex%20as%20India%2C%20very%20little%20can%20be%20achieved%20from%20the%20glass%20and%20chrome%20edifices%20in%20Mumbai%20or%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Nutanben%20and%20her%208-10%20member%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F276231%2Fpune-engineer-helps-maharashtra-villages-become-drought-free-water-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteam%20remain%20resolutely%20focussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20work%20which%20they%20estimate%20will%20need%20another%202-3%20years%20before%20it%20becomes%20self-sustaining.%20She%20knows%20her%20frequent%20trips%20from%20Mumbai%20to%20Aurangabad%20and%20then%20onwards%20into%20the%20nooks%20and%20crannies%20of%20Jalna%20and%20Palghar%20will%20not%20be%20ending%20anytime%20in%20a%20hurry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20filial%20responsibilities%20less%20intense%20than%20in%20the%20past%2C%20she%20can%20afford%20to%20focus%20on%20ameliorating%20the%20water%20woes%20she%20first%20encountered%20when%20she%20landed%20in%20Beed%20seven%20years%20ago.%20In%20terms%20of%20gratification%2C%20anything%20she%20achieves%20in%20Mumbai%20pales%20in%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWritten%20by%20Anjuli%20Bhargava.%20Anjuli%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20columnist%20based%20out%20of%20Goa%20and%20writes%20on%20business%20and%20social%20sector%20issues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697813761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDSC01286_11zon-1697801665.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D332290%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20group%20of%20individuals%20and%20organisations%20partnered%20with%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20to%20bring%20about%20change%20in%20Jalna%20district%20which%20has%20been%20struggling%20with%20water%20scarcity%2C%20drought%20and%20subsequent%20farmer%20suicides%20for%20decades.%22%2C%22author%22%3A